You're always here for me.

25
00:01:09,333 --> 00:01:11,000
You're rock solid.

26
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,875
And best of all,
you laugh at all my jokes.

27
00:01:13,875 --> 00:01:16,000
Bruce, you're a heck of a guy.

28
00:01:16,416 --> 00:01:19,208
But I do wish I had someone
a little prettier to talk to,

29
00:01:19,208 --> 00:01:20,833
like maybe Felicia Hardy.

30
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:23,000
[gentle jazz music]

31
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,291
You're a good dancer.

32
00:01:24,291 --> 00:01:26,208
I love surprises.

33
00:01:26,583 --> 00:01:27,708
What do you think of this one?

34
00:01:29,708 --> 00:01:31,875
[Spider-Man]
Then there's Mary Jane Watson.

35
00:01:31,875 --> 00:01:34,833
Tiger, you just took
the jackpot again.

36
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:36,250
Care to walk me to class?

37
00:01:36,250 --> 00:01:37,583
[Peter] Sure.

38
00:01:37,583 --> 00:01:38,750
[Spider-Man]
What am I thinking?

39
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:40,291
How can anybody commit to a guy

40
00:01:40,291 --> 00:01:41,875
who sneaks off to
crawl on walls?

41
00:01:41,875 --> 00:01:43,083
Hey!

42
00:01:44,250 --> 00:01:45,708
Ow!

43
00:01:45,708 --> 00:01:47,125
I'm losing my grip!

44
00:01:47,125 --> 00:01:48,333
What was that?

45
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:49,583
I never slip.

46
00:01:50,291 --> 00:01:51,583
[gasping]

47
00:01:51,583 --> 00:01:52,708
Got it.

48
00:01:52,708 --> 00:01:54,125
Oh, weird.

49
00:01:54,125 --> 00:01:55,708
Must've been some
kind of glitch.

50
00:01:55,708 --> 00:01:56,750
Oh, no.

51
00:01:56,750 --> 00:01:57,875
It's happening again!

52
00:01:57,875 --> 00:01:59,958
I'm losing my spider powers!

53
00:02:04,875 --> 00:02:06,875
[Spider-Man screams]

54
00:02:07,500 --> 00:02:11,416
I'm sticking again,
but it's too little too late!

55
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:16,750
[loud crash]

56
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:17,958
What's wrong with me?

57
00:02:21,125 --> 00:02:25,958
International smuggling
revenues are up 14%,

58
00:02:25,958 --> 00:02:28,333
theft up 43%.

59
00:02:28,333 --> 00:02:32,833
Fellow crime lords, we are
having a most profitable year.

60
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:34,166
[men laugh]

61
00:02:34,166 --> 00:02:36,875
So it would seem, for now.

62
00:02:36,875 --> 00:02:38,625
But what about the future?

63
00:02:38,625 --> 00:02:39,875
[Kingpin] The future?

64
00:02:40,375 --> 00:02:41,416
[yelps]

65
00:02:41,875 --> 00:02:42,875
[groans]

66
00:02:42,875 --> 00:02:45,000
You dare do this to me?

67
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:48,833
Kingpin, you're losing
control of your territory,

68
00:02:48,833 --> 00:02:52,125
and soon, that's going
to cost us all money!

69
00:02:52,125 --> 00:02:56,291
The crime cartel is
losing respect for you.

70
00:02:56,291 --> 00:02:57,708
-[grunts]
-[electricity crackles]

71
00:02:57,708 --> 00:02:59,583
Losing respect, Silvermane?

72
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:02,583
Who dares defy me now?

73
00:03:02,583 --> 00:03:03,583
Owl?

74
00:03:03,583 --> 00:03:05,416
Maybe you, Hammerhead?

75
00:03:05,416 --> 00:03:09,375
At this very moment,
I've begun an operation

76
00:03:09,375 --> 00:03:13,708
which will exterminate that
wall-crawling vermin forever!

77
00:03:13,708 --> 00:03:16,750
Spider-Man is finished!

78
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:22,833
[lasers buzz]

79
00:03:32,458 --> 00:03:34,083
[device beeping]

80
00:03:34,083 --> 00:03:35,708
[phone beeping]

81
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:38,500
Greetings from the Kingpin,
Chameleon.

82
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:42,208
In 15 minutes, a helicopter
will land in the main yard.

83
00:03:47,125 --> 00:03:48,333
Warden Davis?

84
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:50,166
What are you doing in there?

85
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:54,125
-[belt beeps]
-Warden?

86
00:03:56,583 --> 00:03:57,708
No! [stamemrs]

87
00:03:57,708 --> 00:03:58,875
It can't be!

88
00:03:58,875 --> 00:04:00,375
[Chameleon] Ah, but it is.

89
00:04:04,208 --> 00:04:05,500
The Chameleon's loose!

90
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,583
Help!

91
00:04:08,625 --> 00:04:12,333
[Chameleon] Mac Gargan,
this is your lucky day.

92
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,500
Quentin Beck, follow me.

93
00:04:15,291 --> 00:04:16,416
Shocker?

94
00:04:16,416 --> 00:04:17,583
Get a move on.

95
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:24,583
[Shocker] The Shocker is alive.

96
00:04:25,875 --> 00:04:27,250
[explosion booms]

97
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:28,833
The Scorpion, too.

98
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:30,708
Alive and stinging.

99
00:04:31,125 --> 00:04:36,125
And I can resume my
leading role of Mysterio.

100
00:04:36,125 --> 00:04:38,333
Now, let's disappear.

101
00:04:39,250 --> 00:04:40,708
[guard] Nobody here.

102
00:04:40,708 --> 00:04:41,750
Come on.

103
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:44,875
[Scorpion]
Not bad, bubble head.

104
00:04:44,875 --> 00:04:46,333
Not bad.

105
00:04:47,375 --> 00:04:50,583
Impressive, but why
not try this instead?

106
00:04:50,583 --> 00:04:52,083
It's called a key.

107
00:04:52,083 --> 00:04:53,833
Is it dinner time already?

108
00:04:55,458 --> 00:04:58,458
[Chameleon]
Doctor Octopus, I presume?

109
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:03,416
[explosion booms]

110
00:05:03,416 --> 00:05:05,583
[explosion booms]

111
00:05:05,833 --> 00:05:09,000
[siren wailing]

112
00:05:10,166 --> 00:05:12,875
[guns firing]

113
00:05:23,416 --> 00:05:27,625
[Kingpin] Welcome, Chameleon,
Mysterio, Rhino,

114
00:05:27,833 --> 00:05:31,625
Scorpion, Shocker,
Doctor Octopus,

115
00:05:31,625 --> 00:05:34,333
my insidious six.

116
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:36,750
Your insidious six?

117
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:37,875
Who are you?

118
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:39,375
Why have you brought us here?

119
00:05:39,375 --> 00:05:41,458
[Kingpin] I am your new leader.

120
00:05:41,458 --> 00:05:44,583
All of you are my
ultimate weapon.

121
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:47,208
I ain't nobody's
weapon but my own.

122
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:49,000
[Shocker] Watch your mouth.

123
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,708
Yeah,
that's the Kingpin talking.

124
00:05:51,708 --> 00:05:52,750
The Kingpin?

125
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:54,375
No kidding.

126
00:05:54,375 --> 00:05:56,083
-[Mysterio] Look!
-[Scorpion] Spider-Man?

127
00:05:56,083 --> 00:05:57,583
-Here?
-Get him!

128
00:06:05,083 --> 00:06:07,083
[loud crash]

129
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:15,583
Ooh.

130
00:06:15,583 --> 00:06:17,250
What do you know?

131
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:20,875
All this time, Spider-Man
was really a robot.

132
00:06:20,875 --> 00:06:25,250
Neanderthal, that wasn't
the real Spider-Man.

133
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:26,958
It was an obvious fake!

134
00:06:26,958 --> 00:06:28,000
[doors clack]

135
00:06:30,458 --> 00:06:33,125
So, you're the Kingpin, eh?

136
00:06:33,125 --> 00:06:36,166
While I'm grateful
for the early release,

137
00:06:36,166 --> 00:06:38,708
I have no time for
childish games.

138
00:06:38,708 --> 00:06:41,375
This is no game, I assure you.

139
00:06:41,375 --> 00:06:43,708
It is a demonstration of
what is going to happen

140
00:06:43,708 --> 00:06:45,458
to the real Spider-Man.

141
00:06:45,458 --> 00:06:48,750
First, we will draw him out

142
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:53,375
and then close in
around him like a noose.

143
00:06:53,375 --> 00:06:56,708
Supposing I have
a plan of my own?

144
00:06:56,708 --> 00:06:59,000
[Mysterio]
And I might have one, too.

145
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,291
Solo efforts, I presume?

146
00:07:01,291 --> 00:07:04,708
[Mysterio] He who travels
fastest, travels alone.

147
00:07:04,708 --> 00:07:08,750
Look where you all wound up
when you worked alone, prison.

148
00:07:08,750 --> 00:07:11,125
Gentlemen, we need each other.

149
00:07:11,125 --> 00:07:13,333
With your talents, together,

150
00:07:13,333 --> 00:07:16,291
we're sure to
defeat Spider-Man.

151
00:07:16,291 --> 00:07:19,458
But you must all
agree to follow me.

152
00:07:19,458 --> 00:07:22,083
To the end of the Earth, boss.

153
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:25,625
A man like me could
learn from you, Kingpin.

154
00:07:28,083 --> 00:07:29,750
[Mysterio] The plot
seems clever enough.

155
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:32,583
The climax ought
to be intriguing.

156
00:07:32,583 --> 00:07:35,875
I'd kill for a chance
to work for the Kingpin.

157
00:07:36,625 --> 00:07:38,875
Doctor Octopus?

158
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:41,583
I am no petty hireling.

159
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:43,708
I am a scientist.

160
00:07:43,708 --> 00:07:47,333
I can provide you
with the finest laboratory
in the world

161
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:50,458
and with unlimited resources.

162
00:07:50,458 --> 00:07:53,458
Spider-Man won't
know what hit him.

163
00:07:53,458 --> 00:07:55,583
[Spider-Man]I seem
to have my powers back,

164
00:07:55,583 --> 00:07:58,458
but now, I'm worried about
those six escaped creeps.

165
00:07:58,458 --> 00:08:00,833
[sighs] Can't find a trace
of them anywhere.

166
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:03,583
No bank robberies,
no jewel thefts...

167
00:08:05,208 --> 00:08:06,625
not even any fresh graffiti.

168
00:08:06,625 --> 00:08:08,416
They must be up to something.

169
00:08:08,416 --> 00:08:09,708
I've been searching all night.

170
00:08:09,708 --> 00:08:11,291
Now, it's almost morning.

171
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:12,583
If I'm not back before
Aunt May wakes up,

172
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:13,875
she'll be worried sick.
No.

173
00:08:13,875 --> 00:08:15,000
Not again!

174
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,708
[screams]

175
00:08:16,708 --> 00:08:18,583
[groans]

176
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:19,875
What's happening to me?

177
00:08:21,291 --> 00:08:23,583
I left my clothes
on that high ledge.

178
00:08:23,583 --> 00:08:25,416
Can't get to them now.

179
00:08:25,416 --> 00:08:27,125
I've got to hide.

180
00:08:27,125 --> 00:08:28,708
It'd be too easy for some
super villain to grab me

181
00:08:28,708 --> 00:08:30,083
and take my mask off.

182
00:08:33,708 --> 00:08:35,708
[Aunt May] Peter,
where have you been?

183
00:08:35,708 --> 00:08:36,750
Out jogging.

184
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:38,208
Wearing a blanket?

185
00:08:40,458 --> 00:08:42,291
Are you all right, dear?

186
00:08:42,291 --> 00:08:43,500
Yes, Aunt May.

187
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:45,375
-Fine.
-You look pale to me.

188
00:08:45,375 --> 00:08:48,291
I've just been up all night,
uh, studying.

189
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:51,250
Well, why don't you
just lie down and rest?

190
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:53,166
I'll bring some
breakfast for you.

191
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:54,875
Uh, oh, thanks, Aunt May.

192
00:08:54,875 --> 00:08:56,458
You're the greatest.

193
00:08:56,458 --> 00:08:58,625
[sighs]
I hope rest is all I need.

194
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,083
[groans]

195
00:09:04,083 --> 00:09:05,083
[yawns]

196
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:08,500
Wow, I feel fantastic!

197
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:11,875
Yes, my spider powers are back,
at least for now.

198
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:13,833
Morning, dear.

199
00:09:13,833 --> 00:09:15,500
I'm sorry I let you
sleep like that,

200
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:18,000
but you really must
have needed it.

201
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,625
Sleep like what?

202
00:09:19,625 --> 00:09:22,708
Why, you slept all day
yesterday and all night.

203
00:09:22,708 --> 00:09:23,833
What?

204
00:09:23,833 --> 00:09:26,166
You mean it's Thursday!

205
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:28,708
Well, I tried to wake you
a couple of times,

206
00:09:28,708 --> 00:09:31,875
but you kept turning over
and going back to sleep.

207
00:09:32,208 --> 00:09:34,583
Ah, I'm late
for Dr. Connors's class!

208
00:09:34,583 --> 00:09:36,166
Peter, your breakfast!

209
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:37,500
-Peter!
-[door thuds]

210
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:40,375
Oh, dear me, that boy.

211
00:09:40,375 --> 00:09:44,750
[man] Neogenics,
the new science
of genetic exploration

212
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:47,125
and manipulation of DNA,

213
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:50,625
invented by Professor
Farley Stillwell
here at this college.

214
00:09:50,625 --> 00:09:53,583
It's one of the most important
achievements of this century.

215
00:09:53,583 --> 00:09:56,250
The Toombes Foundation
might be giving

216
00:09:56,250 --> 00:10:00,875
Empire State University
grant money
to continue our research

217
00:10:00,875 --> 00:10:05,166
if we can convince them
how important neogenics is.

218
00:10:05,166 --> 00:10:06,583
That's up to all of us.

219
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:09,458
You are ESU's best
science students.

220
00:10:09,458 --> 00:10:11,333
Consider this a contest.

221
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:14,708
Whoever conceives the most
original neogenics experiment

222
00:10:14,708 --> 00:10:17,375
gets the job as my
research assistant

223
00:10:17,375 --> 00:10:20,750
if the Toombes grant
is awarded to ESU.

224
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:23,000
I'm going to win this, Debra.

225
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:25,583
You'll have to beat me
out first, Michael.

226
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,416
Nice of you to show up, Parker.

227
00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:30,625
Good luck to you all.

228
00:10:30,625 --> 00:10:31,708
-Thank you.
-[Peter sighs]

229
00:10:31,708 --> 00:10:33,375
[Peter thinking] Great.

230
00:10:33,375 --> 00:10:36,000
First, my powers go
wonky, now, this.

231
00:10:37,416 --> 00:10:39,125
A little late, huh, Peter?

232
00:10:39,125 --> 00:10:40,708
What's the matter?

233
00:10:40,708 --> 00:10:43,208
Get wrapped up watching
cartoons this morning?

234
00:10:43,208 --> 00:10:45,125
Not in the mood, Debra.

235
00:10:45,125 --> 00:10:48,000
I had thought you would be
my main competition, Parker,

236
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:51,750
but you will be lucky to
make it to the starting line.

237
00:10:51,750 --> 00:10:54,583
Don't forget, Michael,
the tortoise beat the hare.

238
00:10:54,583 --> 00:10:58,125
In my country,
we eat tortoises.

239
00:10:58,125 --> 00:10:59,166
Peter!

240
00:10:59,166 --> 00:11:00,333
Hi, Felicia.

241
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:03,833
Felicia, what a splendid name.

242
00:11:03,833 --> 00:11:05,875
Allow me to introduce myself.

243
00:11:05,875 --> 00:11:08,416
I am Michael Morbius.

244
00:11:08,416 --> 00:11:09,458
Uh-huh.

245
00:11:09,458 --> 00:11:10,625
Charmed.

246
00:11:10,625 --> 00:11:12,875
Please excuse us.

247
00:11:12,875 --> 00:11:15,875
What B-movie did he come from?

248
00:11:15,875 --> 00:11:18,458
The Revenge of Dracula's Ego.

249
00:11:18,458 --> 00:11:20,458
-What's up?
-I need you to escort me

250
00:11:20,458 --> 00:11:23,416
to the opening of my mother's
new science center tonight.

251
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:24,500
Hah. Wait a minute.

252
00:11:24,500 --> 00:11:26,583
Are you asking me for a date?

253
00:11:26,583 --> 00:11:28,583
Parker, you're the
only one I know

254
00:11:28,583 --> 00:11:31,875
who can explain these boring
science exhibits to me.

255
00:11:31,875 --> 00:11:33,583
Whoa, hold on,
answer the question.

256
00:11:33,583 --> 00:11:34,708
Is it a date?

257
00:11:34,708 --> 00:11:36,166
All right, all right.

258
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:37,625
You can call it a date
if you want.

259
00:11:37,625 --> 00:11:39,458
Great!
I'll be there!

260
00:11:39,458 --> 00:11:40,750
Naturally.

261
00:11:40,750 --> 00:11:44,416
Meet me at The Coffee Bean
at 6:30.

262
00:11:44,416 --> 00:11:45,708
Careful, Felicia.

263
00:11:45,708 --> 00:11:47,708
I don't think he's
had his shots.

264
00:11:47,708 --> 00:11:49,583
Flash, what do you want?

265
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:50,958
I want to know
what Parker's boss

266
00:11:50,958 --> 00:11:52,416
is doing calling those crooks

267
00:11:52,416 --> 00:11:54,875
the Spider-Man Six,
that's what.

268
00:11:54,875 --> 00:11:56,250
The Spider-Man who?

269
00:11:56,250 --> 00:11:58,458
J. Jonah Jameson
is not fooling me.

270
00:11:58,458 --> 00:11:59,958
Spidey's a hero.

271
00:11:59,958 --> 00:12:01,583
He's not any crime boss.

272
00:12:01,583 --> 00:12:02,708
It's some kinda setup.

273
00:12:02,708 --> 00:12:04,375
What are you talking about?

274
00:12:04,708 --> 00:12:06,250
What's the matter, you been
asleep for the past 24 hours?

275
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:08,000
[John]
And here, we see it live,

276
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,750
just as I've always warned you.

277
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:13,500
Spider-Man leading one
of his criminal band,

278
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,708
the Spider-Man Six.

279
00:12:15,708 --> 00:12:16,750
It's a setup, I tell ya.

280
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:18,208
What do you think, Parker?

281
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:19,750
Parker?

282
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:20,875
Where are you?

283
00:12:21,458 --> 00:12:23,083
[Peter thinking] I go to
sleep for one lousy day,

284
00:12:23,083 --> 00:12:24,958
and I wake up
in the Twilight Zone.

285
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:32,708
[Spider-Man]
Hold it, horn head.

286
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:34,333
You didn't fill out
a withdrawal slip.

287
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:36,416
-[Rhino groans]
-The spider has landed.

288
00:12:36,416 --> 00:12:39,166
Get ready
for the Rhino's charge.

289
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:42,750
[loud crash]

290
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:44,375
[Spider-Man groans]

291
00:12:44,375 --> 00:12:46,458
[Spider-Man]
Aren't you a handsome gent?

292
00:12:46,458 --> 00:12:48,000
[gun fires]

293
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:51,625
-[Spider-Man groans]
-Eat acid, Spider-Man.

294
00:12:51,625 --> 00:12:53,958
[acid sizzling]

295
00:12:53,958 --> 00:12:56,125
[Spider-Man] Sorry,
I'm on an acid-free diet.

296
00:12:56,125 --> 00:12:58,125
-[acid sizzling]
-Too many of them.

297
00:12:58,125 --> 00:12:59,291
Got to get clear.

298
00:12:59,458 --> 00:13:01,000
Uh-oh!

299
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,333
-Bad move, Spidey!
-[horn wailing]

300
00:13:02,333 --> 00:13:03,333
Bad move!

301
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:10,166
[Spider-Man] You're getting
predictable, Mysterio!

302
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:12,833
[Mysterio]
Can't have that, can we?

303
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:13,958
[Spider-Man coughing]

304
00:13:13,958 --> 00:13:15,083
[explosion booms]

305
00:13:15,083 --> 00:13:16,458
[Mysterio laughs]

306
00:13:16,458 --> 00:13:18,208
Too bad you didn't predict--

307
00:13:18,208 --> 00:13:19,333
[door thudding]

308
00:13:20,875 --> 00:13:22,875
Hey! He's mine!

309
00:13:22,875 --> 00:13:24,333
Nonsense.

310
00:13:24,333 --> 00:13:26,875
You merely softened
him up for me.

311
00:13:26,875 --> 00:13:29,458
Make way for the Scorpion!

312
00:13:29,458 --> 00:13:33,458
Back off, you pea-brained,
uncoordinated,

313
00:13:33,458 --> 00:13:36,250
absurdly dressed
excuse for a man!

314
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:39,083
Who are you calling
absurdly dressed?

315
00:13:39,083 --> 00:13:40,583
[Doctor Octopus groans]

316
00:13:40,583 --> 00:13:42,250
[Doctor Octopus]
Take your hands off me!

317
00:13:43,250 --> 00:13:46,000
Cease this mindless fighting.

318
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,458
Spider-Man will escape!

319
00:13:47,458 --> 00:13:49,750
[Peter thinking]
Oh, no, not this.

320
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:50,875
Not now!

321
00:13:50,875 --> 00:13:53,000
My powers are gone!

322
00:13:55,875 --> 00:13:56,958
I'm dead meat.

323
00:13:57,583 --> 00:13:59,000
Still got my web-shooters.

324
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:00,708
They're my only chance.

325
00:14:00,708 --> 00:14:04,250
I hate this pathetic gunk.

326
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:05,458
[Spider-Man screams]

327
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:07,333
[Spider-Man groans]

328
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:09,208
Almost tore my arm off!

329
00:14:09,208 --> 00:14:12,000
I better not use webbing again
without my spider-strength.

330
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,000
[loud crash]

331
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:16,583
[loud crash]

332
00:14:18,208 --> 00:14:21,333
[Spider-Man groans]

333
00:14:23,458 --> 00:14:24,458
I can get him!

334
00:14:29,458 --> 00:14:30,458
Huh?

335
00:14:30,458 --> 00:14:31,583
Where'd he go?

336
00:14:32,458 --> 00:14:33,458
[loud clunk]

337
00:14:36,708 --> 00:14:38,208
[Peter thinking]
It's a good thing
I kept my clothes

338
00:14:38,208 --> 00:14:40,000
in a web sack with me
this time.

339
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,833
I have to find out why
I keep losing my powers.

340
00:14:42,833 --> 00:14:45,166
[man]
It's incredible, Spider-Man.

341
00:14:45,166 --> 00:14:47,166
Your DNA structure is changing.

342
00:14:47,166 --> 00:14:48,291
[Spider-Man] Changing?

343
00:14:48,291 --> 00:14:49,833
Into what?

344
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:52,458
Can't say yet,
but I'll help you find out.

345
00:14:52,458 --> 00:14:55,375
I owe you that much for what
you've done for me in the past.

346
00:14:56,625 --> 00:14:59,458
You were not born with your
spider-powers, were you?

347
00:14:59,458 --> 00:15:00,583
[Spider-Man] No.

348
00:15:00,583 --> 00:15:02,083
I won them on a quiz show.

349
00:15:03,208 --> 00:15:04,833
[man] Amazing.

350
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:07,708
These patterns imply
neogenics is involved,

351
00:15:07,708 --> 00:15:09,291
but how could that be?

352
00:15:09,291 --> 00:15:11,000
[Spider-Man] That was
the category I chose.

353
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,958
I need to conduct
some more tests.

354
00:15:13,875 --> 00:15:15,250
[Spider-Man] Fire away.

355
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:19,083
[Peter thinking]
I can't tell him the truth

356
00:15:19,083 --> 00:15:22,208
that neogenics might be
the reason I became Spider-Man.

357
00:15:22,458 --> 00:15:24,375
It was an early experiment
of Farley Stillwell's

358
00:15:24,375 --> 00:15:26,083
that I was watching.

359
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:28,958
Nobody noticed a small
spider climb down

360
00:15:28,958 --> 00:15:31,458
into the path of
his radioactive ray.

361
00:15:33,333 --> 00:15:35,333
[Farley] The future
of genetic engineering

362
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:39,500
lies in unraveling
the mystery of DNA.

363
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:42,166
[Peter thinking] That spider
changed my life forever.

364
00:15:42,166 --> 00:15:43,583
-[chomps softly]
-[Peter gasps]

365
00:15:43,583 --> 00:15:44,708
[groans]

366
00:15:46,708 --> 00:15:49,208
[Spider-Man]
Doc, what's going on with me?

367
00:15:49,208 --> 00:15:51,625
I need to do more tests
to be sure,

368
00:15:51,625 --> 00:15:54,750
but your DNA may have
mutated permanently.

369
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:58,208
For all I know,
your powers will be gone.

370
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:01,208
Enough!

371
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:03,208
Scour the city.

372
00:16:03,208 --> 00:16:07,833
Find that wall-crawling
worm at all costs.

373
00:16:23,208 --> 00:16:25,708
[Peter thinking]
So, it's over, just like that.

374
00:16:25,708 --> 00:16:27,458
I'm not Spider-Man anymore.

375
00:16:27,458 --> 00:16:29,458
Now, I'm just normal.

376
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:32,875
I guess I'm finally free!

377
00:16:32,875 --> 00:16:34,958
No more danger,
no more secrets.

378
00:16:34,958 --> 00:16:36,708
Time to study,
go out on dates!

379
00:16:36,708 --> 00:16:38,125
Oh, no.

380
00:16:38,125 --> 00:16:39,291
Felicia!

381
00:16:46,583 --> 00:16:50,291
Now, where could an inane
arachnid aberration

382
00:16:50,291 --> 00:16:53,250
such as you be going in
so much of a hurry?

383
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:55,833
Out of my way, Octopus!

384
00:16:56,875 --> 00:16:58,750
You didn't say please.

385
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:01,625
Now, must I repeat my question?

386
00:17:01,625 --> 00:17:03,500
No, I'll tell you.

387
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:05,375
I'm headed for
Peter Parker's house.

388
00:17:05,375 --> 00:17:07,458
He's this newspaper
photographer,

389
00:17:07,458 --> 00:17:08,833
always shooting Spider-Man.

390
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:09,875
Parker?

391
00:17:09,875 --> 00:17:13,000
Yes, I know who he is.

392
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,583
I figured I'd follow him.

393
00:17:14,583 --> 00:17:16,166
Maybe he'll lead me
to the wall-crawler.

394
00:17:16,166 --> 00:17:17,958
Hmm, good plan.

395
00:17:17,958 --> 00:17:21,125
Too good for a clod
such as yourself.

396
00:17:21,125 --> 00:17:24,291
Follow me and see how
a master would do it.

397
00:17:26,875 --> 00:17:28,333
I don't know where Peter is.

398
00:17:28,333 --> 00:17:30,000
Frankly, dear,
I'm getting worried.

399
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:32,875
Well, if he gets in soon,
please have him call me.

400
00:17:32,875 --> 00:17:35,166
Thank you, goodbye.

401
00:17:35,166 --> 00:17:36,833
[Felicia thinking] I'd worry
if he was ever on time.

402
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:38,416
What do you got
in the purse, honey?

403
00:17:38,416 --> 00:17:40,708
-I take all major credit cards.
-[gasps]

404
00:17:40,708 --> 00:17:41,958
[Felicia] No!

405
00:17:42,458 --> 00:17:45,625
-This does not belong to you!
-[grunts]

406
00:17:45,625 --> 00:17:46,708
Let go of that or I'm gonna--

407
00:17:46,708 --> 00:17:47,750
[siren wailing]

408
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:50,000
[indistinct radio chatter]

409
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,333
[Felicia] Are you all right?

410
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:53,208
Yes, of course.

411
00:17:53,208 --> 00:17:56,875
Ah, it is you,
Parker's girlfriend, huh?

412
00:17:56,875 --> 00:17:58,708
I'm not Parker's girlfriend.

413
00:17:58,708 --> 00:18:01,125
I'm not even sure
I want to be his friend.

414
00:18:01,125 --> 00:18:04,166
Felicia,
you shouldn't be out alone

415
00:18:04,166 --> 00:18:06,458
at night in this neighborhood.

416
00:18:06,458 --> 00:18:09,083
You know something, Michael,
you're right.

417
00:18:09,083 --> 00:18:10,833
How would you like
to keep me company?

418
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:13,583
I would be delighted.

419
00:18:13,583 --> 00:18:15,208
Naturally.

420
00:18:15,208 --> 00:18:18,708
Tell me, what do you
know about science?

421
00:18:19,375 --> 00:18:20,833
-[doorbell rings]
-Peter?

422
00:18:23,708 --> 00:18:25,416
Oh, can I help you?

423
00:18:25,416 --> 00:18:27,375
Allow me to introduce myself.

424
00:18:27,375 --> 00:18:29,625
I am Doctor Otto Octavius.

425
00:18:29,625 --> 00:18:30,875
A doctor?

426
00:18:30,875 --> 00:18:32,500
It's about Peter, isn't it?

427
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,333
I knew he looked ill.
Where is he?

428
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:37,500
[stammers]
Uh, Peter collapsed
on the street.

429
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:40,000
Fortunately, it
was near my clinic.

430
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,125
Good heavens!

431
00:18:41,125 --> 00:18:42,416
Take me to him.

432
00:18:42,416 --> 00:18:43,833
But of course.

433
00:18:47,291 --> 00:18:49,416
Aunt May!
No dinner for me tonight!

434
00:18:49,416 --> 00:18:51,458
I'm late! Aunt May?

435
00:18:51,458 --> 00:18:52,708
[Peter thinking]
She's always home
at this time of night.

436
00:18:53,291 --> 00:18:55,583
Why do I think if I still
had my spider-sense,

437
00:18:56,291 --> 00:18:58,000
it'd be going crazy right now?

438
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:59,125
Aunt May?!

439
00:19:00,458 --> 00:19:01,458
Aunt May!

440
00:19:04,208 --> 00:19:06,166
[Peter reading] " Parker,
if you ever want to see

441
00:19:06,166 --> 00:19:09,000
your Aunt May again, tell
your friend Spider-Man

442
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:13,000
he's wanted at 636 Battery
Street immediately."

443
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,708
Aunt May.

444
00:19:14,708 --> 00:19:16,000
[Peter thinking] Even
without my powers,

445
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,750
I can't fail her now.

446
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:19,458
[Aunt May] Doctor, tell me more
about Peter's condition.

447
00:19:19,458 --> 00:19:21,458
Well, it is precarious.

448
00:19:21,458 --> 00:19:22,875
Oh, dear.

449
00:19:22,875 --> 00:19:23,958
When can I see him?

450
00:19:23,958 --> 00:19:25,833
Soon.

451
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:28,750
We have the best doctors
attending to him
at this clinic.

452
00:19:28,750 --> 00:19:31,333
How ironic, the Kingpin
built this clinic

453
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:33,166
to patch up his men.

454
00:19:33,166 --> 00:19:36,416
Yet look how perfectly
it serves our little charade.

455
00:19:36,416 --> 00:19:39,333
[Scorpion] I think the old bat
is sweet on the Doc.

456
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:41,250
[Shocker]
Here comes Spider-Man.

457
00:19:43,833 --> 00:19:45,708
Hmm.

458
00:19:45,708 --> 00:19:47,625
Never seen Spider-Man
come in on foot before.

459
00:19:47,625 --> 00:19:50,000
He must have some
trick up his sleeve.

460
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,583
[device beeping]

461
00:19:51,583 --> 00:19:53,125
Excuse me, my dear.

462
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:56,250
I am needed in surgery,
but I'll be back.

463
00:19:57,625 --> 00:19:59,375
What a nice man.

464
00:20:11,083 --> 00:20:13,000
[Spider-Man screams]

465
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,375
[groans]

466
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:17,291
[Peter thinking] Oh, no!

467
00:20:17,875 --> 00:20:21,458
[Mysterio]
No more illusions, Spider-Man.

468
00:20:21,458 --> 00:20:23,125
We're real.

469
00:20:23,125 --> 00:20:25,583
And we got you at last.

470
00:20:25,583 --> 00:20:27,583
Oh, you poor dear.

471
00:20:27,583 --> 00:20:31,875
Ready for the end, my pretty?

472
00:20:32,125 --> 00:20:34,375
[laughs loudly]

473
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,875
["Spider-Man Theme Song"
playing]

474
00:20:49,625 --> 00:20:53,333
♪ Spider-Man, Spider-Man ♪

475
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:57,291
♪ Radioactive Spider-Man ♪

476
00:20:58,166 --> 00:20:59,625
[guitar solo]

477
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:07,708
♪ Spider blood, spider blood ♪

478
00:21:07,708 --> 00:21:09,875
♪ Radioactive spider blood ♪

479
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:11,708
♪ Spider blood, spider blood ♪

480
00:21:11,708 --> 00:21:13,250
♪ Spider-Man ♪

